│ collected guards for this predecessor, reuse them.\n       auto It =                       │
│ CachedLoopGuards.find(Pred);\n       if (It != CachedLoopGuards.end()) {\n\n```\n\nThis    │
│ change is placed at the beginning of the lambda function that processes each predecessor.  │
│ It adds a guard that prevents the analysis from proceeding down a path that starts with an │
│ unreachable block, thereby breaking the infinite recursion.\n\n### 5. Conclusion\n\nThe    │
│ crash is due to a stack overflow caused by an infinite recursion in ScalarEvolution's      │
│ `LoopGuards` analysis. The recursion is triggered by malformed IR containing a PHI node    │
│ with an operand from an unreachable basic block. The proposed fix corrects the analysis by │
│ making it robust to this specific form of invalid IR, ensuring it skips unreachable paths  │
│ and terminates correctly. This resolves the crash and allows the `nary-reassociate` pass   │
