╭─ Assistant [MainThread@1688120] ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ An analysis of the bug reveals a stack overflow due to infinite recursion in               │
│ `ScalarEvolution`. This occurs when processing a `phi` node that has an incoming value     │
│ from an unreachable basic block. The `LoopGuards` analysis in `ScalarEvolution`            │
│ recursively tries to collect facts from predecessor blocks but fails to terminate when one │
│ of them is unreachable, as it's not properly handled in the control flow graph traversal.  │
│                                                                                            │
│ The fix is to add a check within `ScalarEvolution::LoopGuards::collectFromPHI` to identify │
│ and ignore incoming values from unreachable blocks. A block is considered unreachable if   │
│ it has no predecessors and is not the entry block of the function. This check prevents the │
│ analysis from descending into an invalid path, thus breaking the infinite recursion.       │
│                                                                                            │
│ I will now apply this fix.                                                                 │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```patch                                                                                   │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Analysis/ScalarEvolution.cpp                                                │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Analysis/ScalarEvolution.cpp                                                │
│ @@ -15348,9 +15348,14 @@                                                                   │
│                                                                                            │
│    using MinMaxPattern = std::pair<const SCEVConstant *, SCEVTypes>;                       │
│    auto GetMinMaxConst = [&](unsigned IncomingIdx) -> MinMaxPattern {                      │
│ -    const BasicBlock *InBlock = Phi.getIncomingBlock(IncomingIdx);                        │
│ +    BasicBlock *InBlock = Phi.getIncomingBlock(IncomingIdx);                              │
│ +    // If the predecessor is unreachable, we can't collect any guards from it.            │
│ +    if (pred_empty(InBlock) &&                                                            │
│ +        !InBlock->isEntryBlock())                                                         │
│ +      return {nullptr, scCouldNotCompute};                                                │
│      if (!VisitedBlocks.insert(InBlock).second)                                            │
│        return {nullptr, scCouldNotCompute};                                                │
│ +                                                                                          │
│      auto [G, Inserted] = IncomingGuards.try_emplace(InBlock, LoopGuards(SE));             │
│      if (Inserted)                                                                         │
│        collectFromBlock(SE, G->second, Phi.getParent(), InBlock, VisitedBlocks,            │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                        │
